School camp was one disaster after another.
And then my mild cold turned into a full-blown flu.
It all ended with me going straight to the hospital.
they came to pay me a visit back then.
There is no one else here, is there?
Who do you think is paying for it?
It did not have to be such a fancy single bed room.
The nurses are gossiping about how I may be the hospital director's bastard son.
The girls thought you were going to die.
Your father was the one who paid for my hospital expenses, too, was not he?
Which basically means we paid for them.
I did not think anyone could be such a brat.
I never thought you, of all people, would be the one to come visit me, though.
Shoot, I have to get going!
Do not you dare tell anyone about this, all right?
Uesugi-san, have you seen Nino here?
I have not seen you since school camp.
I am glad you are alive, at least.
Who ever asked you to come?
We were not sure you were going to make it, at one point.
Your temperature was as high as a record-breaking summer day.
I am glad you are better.
You can call if you ever get lonely.
We will come take care of you.
But I prefer being by myself.
Handouts from class while you were sick.
Good thing I finally got them to you.
So you are going to school, huh?
You were never that committed, were you?
Come on, you are so mean.
That I would not have any problem quitting.
But I am going to stay a little longer.
There is something I cannot leave behind now.
You are aloof, insensitive, and mean.
does it have to be you?
Was there something you did not like?
I would have cooked for you if you would asked me.
No, I just do not really have an appetite.
Well, we would better be going.
I hope you get better soon.
You are being discharged tomorrow, are not you, Uesugi-kun?
Are you worried about your studies?
but there are some idiots that I have to teach.
I guess I should thank them for coming to visit.
You are never going to get your ears pierced if you are afraid of needles.
What are you guys actually here for?
We always get vaccinated around this time every year.
But Itsuki and Nino keep running away.
I am glad we got to see Uesugi-san while we were at it, though.
You are going to get it!
I expect great things from you.
I feel like I have seen that man somewhere.
It was a long time ago.
But it is a scene that is etched firmly in my mind.
Oh, it is just you, Itsuki.
Do not scare me like that.
Th-That is for me to say.
Yotsuba and the others have been looking for you.
I do not know what you are talking about.
I am here to ask you a question.
Tell me: why do you study?
Because that is my job as a student.
I am going to keep staring at you until you tell me the truth.
Want me to keep staring at you until you give up?
We will see who surrenders first.
I am not leaving until you tell me.
That means you are getting the dare.
I have not been able to eat fish since last time!
We are on a school trip!
Stop being a goody-two-shoes and join us!
You should invite Sanada-kun, too, though.
It is the five of us in this group.
Throw out all your useless junk!
For me, this is the only thing that matters.
I swiped it from my dad's work stuff.
Those two have known each other since they were little.
They live nearby, and their parents are close, too.
Their families have gone on trips together, even.
And they are both class reps.
My stomach started hurting all of a sudden.
I need to hit the bathroom.
Throw out all your useless junk!
You took a picture of me just now, did not you?
This kid fell for my beauty!
He took sneak pictures of me!
Let us check his camera, then.
I am sorry, would you mind showing it to me?
An unidentified flying object has emerged over Japan!
We come from the planet of Shogi.
The most capable player in Japan shall play me for the fate of planet Earth.
And that is how my school trip ended.
That is the part I wanted to hear about!
And you ended it so abruptly!
I never said I would tell you.
The only reason I did what you asked
was to thank you for coming the other day.
You did not sound that grateful.
But I can see that you have changed a great deal since then.
That meeting that girl changed you.
Do you think I can change, too?
I would like you to help me change, if you could.
You are looking for someone, right?
We are both alone and lonely.
Hey, let us have our picture taken.
Dude, I never said you could touch it!
Is there any use in having me teach you?
Your average test score is a 29.6.
We will do everything we can.
I dug up my old lucky charm.
Oh, yeah, that girl bought similar ones, too.
Wait, where did you buy those?
I do not remember if I bought them or if someone gave them to me.
I think they are from Kyoto, five years ago.
We went looking all over for you.
Let us go, now that the five of us are all here.
Itsuki, I am going to do it!
And you are going down with me!
It has to be a coincidence, right?
You just got out of the hospital.
Why did you want us all to wear our hair the same way?
You are not tutoring us today?
Without any hints, I do not know who is who.
You are like one of those recent idol groups!
I think that is just because you are disinterested.
This happened just ten minutes ago.
And she went to the trouble of tearing her name off every sheet.
I could not tell who it was because she was in a bath towel,
but the culprit is among us.
You are just going to assume it was me?!
So that is why you had us all do our hair the same way.
How do you tell each other apart just by your faces?
Who else but Miku has such a bland face?
No one else but Nino has such an annoying face.
And what do you mean by annoying?
Uesugi-san, let me tell you something useful.
You are bland because you are bland!
Our mother taught us how to tell each other apart a long time ago.
Love will show you the way!
No wonder I could not tell.
Can we let our hair down now?
Why are you so serious today?
I need you to do something for me.
It did not sound so hurtful.
You can tell us apart by our moles.
I would not mind showing you, Futaro.
It is not going to help if you have not seen the culprit's mole, is it?
Futaro-kun, it could be that the culprit is not among us.
We are sextuplets and have a secret sixth sister, Mutsumi!
She is in a secret room, unknown to any of us.
This problem set has questions from the earlier exams.
The one who does the worst is the culprit.
Why do we have to do this?
I panicked and kicked you out in a hurry,
but that seems to have worked to my advantage.
I would let my guard down on the quiz, but I can do well if I try.
Sorry, everyone, let us get this over with.
He is casually going to compare our handwriting.
I am the only one who can dry my hair so quickly.
I wish I would had some more time to get dressed, but...
You will fail because you do not pay enough attention to girls.
The way you write the letter b.
I remembered you were the only one who writes it cursive.
I do not know you well enough to tell apart your faces,
but I have seen your handwriting more often than I would like.
The rest of us finished, too.
Itsuki's so is the same as the culprit.
They are all the same as the culprit's!
Each one of you failed a quiz!
You were supposed to hide them before he got here!
I am in the hospital for a while, and this is what happens?
I do not know if you are all...
The reason you were trying so hard to tell us apart...
It has something to do with that girl from five years ago you mentioned, right?
You think it is one of us, do not you?
What is the point in buying all of those?
This is to make me try five times harder.
I am going to become an example for the others.
Raise your hand if you met me a long time ago.
There is no way that girl was one of you idiots.
Assumes she looks like this now
H-How dare you call us idiots?!
I am not wrong, am I?
I cannot believe you have been hiding the exams you bombed.
We are spending all day today on review.
I do not care about you anymore, Futaro.
It looks like you need to do some studying first, Uesugi-san.
Though now that I take a good look,
I do not think I am going to be able to tell them apart without their handwriting.
